    59	#: 21220 S13/Virtual Reality
    60	    08-Nov-91  18:08:55
    61	Sb: #Welcome!
    62	Fm: John Eagan 76130,2225
    63	To: all
    64	
    65	Hello, and welcome to the Virtual Reality section of COMART, our newest
    66	section. I've been drafted as the section head, and hope to be able to help
    67	guide things along as we work on bringing VR to personal computers in the way
    68	FRACTINT and DKB and VIVID have brought fractals and raytracing within the
    69	grasp of people with basic DOS machines. All suggestions are welcome. I've
    70	uploaded a basic introduction to the section as VRINTRO.ZIP / VRINTRO.DOC .
    71	Take a look at it and fire away!
    72	        For a start, it appears that people are working on interfaces for the
    73	Mattel "Power Glove",if you have any source code and/or executable files for
    74	such an interface, or anything else relevant to virtual reality, let's see it.
    75	As things progress we plan to get a work group started somewhat along the same
    76	philosophy as the the now-legendary<g>   "Stone Soup Group.  I propose that we
    77	use C as the standard language for our project (projects?) because of its
    78	popularity, somewhat modular nature, and the fact that I have TurboC++ !
    79	Obviously, for reasons of speed, assembler code will probably be necessary at
    80	some point, but that should work out fine with the assembler routines compiled
    81	into .OBJ files. Myself, I'm a real novice programmer, so if anyone feels up
    82	to the challenge of heading up a project, step right up and announce yourself.
    83	My role will be to act as a coordinator and director,   mostly; in fact, my
    84	hope is to be able to get things rolling to the point where I can sit back and
    85	concentrate on "overview" mode. Hope to hear from all of you. Let's have some
    86	fun in cyberspace!
    87	JLE 
    88	
    89	There is 1 Reply.
