   219	#: 21280 S13/Virtual Reality
   220	    10-Nov-91  02:40:48
   221	Sb: #21233-#great timing
   222	Fm: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147
   223	To: John Swenson 75300,2136 (X)
   224	
   225	John & John -
   226	 
   227	The 3D glasses are indeed LCD shutters, sold by Sega to go with their video
   228	game system.  You can't find them in the stores anymore, but you can order
   229	them direct from Sega (800-872-7342) for $35 (+ about $2 S&H).  Delivery is
   230	quoted at 4-6 weeks, but I got mine in about 2.  VISA cheerfully accepted.
   231	 
   232	There was a schematic for driving the glasses posted on UseNet back in Jan of
   233	1990.  (I've been wanting to do this for a -long- time).  The design was for
   234	interfacing with the Mac serial port, but with some minor mods it seems to
   235	work just dandy off a PC parallel port.  If you have some CMOS in your junkbox,
   236	wirewrap tools in your toolbox, and know which end of a soldering iron to hold,
   237	you're all set.  I would have uploaded the schematic already, but I'll have to
   238	dig through the accompanying docs for copyright notices, etc.
   239	 
   240	The cord from the glasses terminates in a 1/8" stereo plug, which plugs into a
   241	little "interface block", which plugs into the game (I assume, I've never seen
   242	the game unit).  The schematic was for interfacing via the plug, and made no
   243	mention of this block thing.  To save a trip to Radio Shack I was going to
   244	scavenge the 1/8" jack off the block, but when I opened it up I found a little
   245	circuit board inside.  The numbers on the chips lead me to believe that this
   246	itself is the required interface, and the circuit I had just painstakingly
   247	assembled was redundant.  The block is just crying to be reverse engineered;
   248	anybody up for it?
   249	 
   250	For software, it's just a matter of doing "page flipping" and tickling bits
   251	on the parallel port.  Yes indeed, 3D FractInt creations, and raytraces,
   252	look -great- in color.
   253	       
   254	
   255	There are 3 Replies.
