   300	Mike- Great! I didn't know about these, that's just what we need. You can't
   301	get them in stores anywhere? That's a shame. Are these color,do I understand
   302	correctly?    I have,in my hot little hands, C source code for a Mattel
   303	Powerglove interface, courtesy of Chris Babcock. I plan to upload it, once I'm
   304	sure about copyright and all (it's a little vague,  although Chris says it's
   305	OK, I'm guessing he has had contact. It also could use a couple of
   306	modifications, but Chris also tells me there is updated code on the way. I
   307	want ot compile and upload it as an executable,along with the source. The
   308	glove hardware interface uses RS-232. It looks like we have a good start! Once
   309	we get all the hardware info in the lib here, we can dive into getting it all
   310	integrated. Then we can work on some software for the thing.  Any ideas in
   311	particular about what we should actually DO with it,  once we get the hardware
   312	working?  Another thing about the hardware.  It looks as if maybe,to integrate
   313	the glove and glasses interfaces,  we might want to work on a design for a
   314	card to plug in an expansion slot with connections for the glove and glasses.
   315	We'll have to discuss that. I just got a copy of TurboCAD, so I can help lay
   316	out a board, rather than messing with wire-wrap (ARG!). Not that laying out a
   317	board is EASY, but for everyone else, it would be a little easier for everyone
   318	else if there was a way to get a board made from available artwork.
   319	JLE-VRsection 
