   429	#: 21324 S13/Virtual Reality
   430	    10-Nov-91  23:22:49
   431	Sb: #21298-#great timing
   432	Fm: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147
   433	To: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225 (X)
   434	
   435	> Are these color, do I understand correctly?
   436	 
   437	They're just electronic sunglasses, where each lens can be made clear or opaque,
   438	quickly, in sync with an image on a crt.  Any color you see comes through the
   439	lenses from the monitor, not from the glasses themselves.
   440	 
   441	I have been having some problems with the C source for the PowerGlove; my
   442	results are just not as good as what Chris is reporting.  My feeling has
   443	been that the low-level interface to the glove should be done with a simple
   444	cpu, as you suggest, to take some of the load off the pc.  With this thought
   445	in mind, I showed the glove to a friend who programs 8031's for living (simple,
   446	cheap, single chip computers).  He was impressed, and went out the next day
   447	and bought a glove for himself.  I next showed the thing to another buddy who
   448	does circuit board layouts for a living; he bought one too.  I just may turn
   449	my complete attention to the glasses and sit back and see what these two guys
   450	come up with.
   451	 
   452	Tom Sawyer
   453	VP, Fence Painting Div.
   454	       
