   574	#: 21348 S13/Virtual Reality
   575	    11-Nov-91  13:26:45
   576	Sb: #21321-#great timing
   577	Fm: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147
   578	To: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225 (X)
   579	
   580	One of the problems with going to an expansion slot card is that it would be
   581	useful only to those with IBM machines, whereas going with RS232 would open
   582	things up to all sorts of folks.  The headache of trying to decide which
   583	COM port to use could be helped by a cheap A-B switchbox.
   584	 
   585	Another concern I have is how to design a slot card that won't bump into other
   586	things, like com ports, parallel ports, video cards, lan cards, music boards,
   587	John's raytrace accelerator board <g>, etc.  It seems like it would take a lot
   588	of research to find safe, unused io ports or memory areas that wouldn't cause
   589	a conflict.  Maybe someone with some pc hardware savvy could dispel my fears
   590	on this.
   591	 
   592	Just playin' devil's advocate.
   593	       
   594	
   595	There is 1 Reply.
   596	
   597	#: 21349 S13/Virtual Reality
   598	    11-Nov-91  13:26:51
   599	Sb: #21320-great timing
   600	Fm: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147
   601	To: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225 (X)
   602	
   603	The back side of the block has a piece of circuit board sticking out a couple
   604	of inches.  The board is 2" wide, with 2 rows of gold plated card edge fingers
   605	on the end, .1" centers, staggard.  17 contacts on the inside row, 18 on the
   606	outside.
   607	             |   v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v  |
   608	             |  v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v v |
   609	             +--------------------------------------+
   610	 
   611	BTW, the original circuit design, by Juri Menkki, includes a copyright, so
   612	I've sent him email requesting permission to post it.  Hopefully the address
   613	I have for him is current, and the connection to Finland will work.  I'll let
   614	you know as soon as I hear back from him.
   615	       
