   617	#: 21350 S13/Virtual Reality
   618	    11-Nov-91  13:26:58
   619	Sb: #21327-#great timing
   620	Fm: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147
   621	To: John Swenson 75300,2136 (X)
   622	
   623	Keep in mind these aren't something you'd find in use at JPL; you get what you
   624	pay for.  Even when the lenses are clear they're as dark as sunglasses.  This
   625	may be by design, to cut contrast for reducing flicker.  I'm tempted to
   626	disect them to remove the LCDs and trash the dark plastic, but the plastic
   627	itself might be polarized and part of the whole scheme of things.  In the mean
   628	time I just keep the monitor's brightness pegged, and the room lights off.
   629	 
   630	Beyond that, they're not terribly comfortable, and look pretty ridiculous when
   631	worn by an adult (though not as strange as R/B glasses, or for that matter, a
   632	Power Glove).  But as you say, for $35, get two.  I'm thinking of getting a
   633	second pair...watching the screen flicker two images back and forth while
   634	someone else has the glasses on really does cause headaches.
