   644	
   645	Speaking of Fractint, I've been using "Stereo: 3=photo" in the 3D Mode
   646	Selection menu and the images come out filling the screen from edge to edge.
   647	The Image Crop parameters on the Funny Glasses Parameters only seem to work
   648	for Red/Blue stereo types 1 & 2 (alternate & superimpose).  As expected the
   649	3D-ness goes completly out of whack around the edges.  Is there a way to force
   650	this cropping for type 3?  I guess a piclab script is the way to go for the
   651	time being, but I'm not sure just how much to crop and where.
   652	 
   653	I hope I've been using the term "page flipping" right.  By that do you mean
   654	getting both images loaded into the vga and fiddling the Start Address
   655	Register?  If so, yes, it seems to be fast enough, but getting it timed right
   656	with the LCDs seems to take a little fudging.  Right now I'm just using
   657	idiot-loop delays tuned from the keyboard, but some accurate msec delays and
   658	hooks into vertical retrace (or sync, or whatever) might improve things.
