   757	#: 21383 S13/Virtual Reality
   758	    11-Nov-91  19:53:24
   759	Sb: #21348-#great timing
   760	Fm: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225
   761	To: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147 (X)
   762	
   763	Mike- Good points,all. I'm not a hardware designer, but I have enough
   764	electronics schooling to know that you're very right about designing a card
   765	that won't be fighting for addresses and interrupts. Big project,  no doubt.
   766	Plus the added disadvantage that people would have to make, or get made, a
   767	board, instead of just plugging in! As far as RS-232 vs.  IBM-compatible card
   768	goes, I'm thinking in terms of us developing software to go with it, for DOS.
   769	So the "exclusivity"  wouldn't bother me, as far as that is concerned. A
   770	switch box is a good idea, it would solve my problem at least (I mean, I
   771	wouldn't use the mouse AND P.G. at the same time,right?)    My concern is that
   772	if we end up with,say, a system that uses the power glove WITH glasses,  we'd
   773	be tying up plugs on the machine fast, and most of all, the speed problem. I
   774	suspect you hardware buddies would come up with a direct-buss interface
   775	because of speed. If that route is taken (and believe me, the trouble and $$
   776	of getting a board made would not be a treat) I suppose we'd need some sort of
   777	"install" software, to negotiate interrupts and addresses and stuff.  Play
   778	devil's advocate,  we need that.
   779	JLE 
