   981	#: 21446 S13/Virtual Reality
   982	    12-Nov-91  19:21:22
   983	Sb: #21375-#Virtual Reality Forum
   984	Fm: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225
   985	To: Chris 76166,1257 (X)
   986	
   987	Chris- Glad to have you with us. We're just getting started here,  this
   988	section just opened this past weekend! So if you would like to get involved,
   989	you're certainly in at the ground floor. Sounds like you've got just the
   990	background we're looking for. We're just discussing some basics right now,
   991	feeling around for what hardware we can use, etc. I've written a short intro
   992	available in lib 13 as VRINTR.ZIP (or) VRINTR.DOC , just to give you a feel
   993	for what we want to do. In short, while there will almost certainly be
   994	discussion and philisophical ramblings, the main purpose is to try to bring VR
   995	to the average DOS-based PC.  Definitely NOT $50K-plus systems! e.g.,I have a
   996	12MHz 286 with 1MB of RAM. No Cray here!! Of course, my machine is pretty
   997	low-end, but we want to shoot for that sort of level.    Feel free to
   998	contribute any files you might have, and jump right in to the message threads.
   999	We already have messages on the board from several people who have been very
  1000	active on the graphics forums, including the Stone Soup Group, the bunch
  1001	responsible for FRACTINT. BTW,please go to the "change forum options"  menu
  1002	and add your last name, so we can keep things clear as the messages pile up.
  1003	John Eagan-VR section leader 
