  1028	#: 21454 S13/Virtual Reality
  1029	    12-Nov-91  21:29:55
  1030	Sb: #21445-#great timing
  1031	Fm: Bill Pulver 70405,1152
  1032	To: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225 (X)
  1033	
  1034	John, (& Mike),
  1035	       DONT rip the suckers apart! Thats exactly how an LCD display works. The
  1036	incoming light is polarized as it passes thru the active areas of the
  1037	"crystal". The active areas are either "on" or "off" (obviously <g>). The
  1038	crystal when "on" polarizes the light 90 deg away from the orientation of the
  1039	"film" polarizer stuck (with one *tough* adhesive!) to the outside of the
  1040	cell. Thus when "on" the light is blocked, "off" it is polarized on the way
  1041	out but still passed, albiet somewhat dimmer. I've ordered a pair too, should
  1042	have them soon!
  1043	
  1044	Later --- Bill
  1045	
  1046	
