  1074	#: 21467 S13/Virtual Reality
  1075	    12-Nov-91  23:00:05
  1076	Sb: #21447-#Virtual Reality Forum
  1077	Fm: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225
  1078	To: Chris Eisnaugle 76166,1257 (X)
  1079	
  1080	Chris- OK, good to have another opinion about "to board or not to board".
  1081	About the system compatibility issue, I think an important consideration is
  1082	that we ought to steer activity toward DOS platform.  Mind you, I'm not going
  1083	to try to discourage general development, and there is room for several
  1084	different projects here.  But we should think in terms of software. The
  1085	general goal is to try to get VR working,  which implies more than just pieces
  1086	of hardware,  but some kind of application as well. Which brings us back to
  1087	platform. But we're pretty open . Perhaps, what we need is to develop a
  1088	consensus on a couple of pieces of hardware, and then any software projects
  1089	could take off from there using a common "standard". DOS machines are the most
  1090	common, and the work in the forum in general is pretty much DOS based, with
  1091	few exceptions.  But keep those ideas coming. The co-processor idea is
  1092	interesting, would you elaborate on any ideas? I saw something about TI
  1093	graphics processors in May DDJ,  what do you know about them? (TI340XX series)
  1094	There is, at this point, no formal "viewing helmet" underway,  although that
  1095	seems to me like a good project, one I'd like to see. If you have a proposal,
  1096	you can always upload it to the lib, since the message space is kind of small,
  1097	and also messages go away with age!  After a few weeks of kicking things
  1098	around, I'll look at what's on the table and offer my two cents about where we
  1099	seem to be going.
