  1184	#: 21480 S13/Virtual Reality
  1185	    13-Nov-91  05:41:11
  1186	Sb: #21466-#great timing
  1187	Fm: John Swenson 75300,2136
  1188	To: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225 (X)
  1189	
  1190	I think one of the best uses of this (particularlyy in the short term) will
  1191	be the interface for the wireframe modeler being worked on over in POV land.
  1192	I think you have to be careful that VR be used for something that it is GOOD
  1193	at, not just as a new fangled interface for something that already works
  1194	well. For example I personally would NOT go to the trouble to put on gloves
  1195	and glasses to run TAPCIS (it works fine just the way it is). But it would be
  1196	the "only game in town" for things like the 3d modeler, specifying the path
  1197	for a "flyby" of a julibrot etc.
  1198	 
  1199	It would also have a great use in scientific analysis software. Displaying
  1200	and analyzing graphs of many variables is traditionally a very tough job,
  1201	with VR you could do a true 3D graph, and the user can go right inside the
  1202	graph and move around in the "graph" space. (business types could also use
  1203	this alot. I can just see the multi-megabuck version of the hardware being
  1204	used at the "anual meeting" to show the financial graphs to the stockholders)
  1205	 
  1206	This is where I think the initial energies should be focused, on things that
  1207	cannot be done very well by any of the more "traditional" methods.
  1208	 
  1209	Focusing on applications such as the TAPCIS interface is just going to get
  1210	us labeled as a bunch of crazy fools rather than making significant
  1211	improvements in the computing environment.
  1212	 
  1213	John S.
  1214	       
