  1218	#: 21481 S13/Virtual Reality
  1219	    13-Nov-91  05:41:19
  1220	Sb: #21418-#VR demo received today
  1221	Fm: John Swenson 75300,2136
  1222	To: Matt Drury 75300,1610 (X)
  1223	
  1224	Oops,
  1225	I replied to John rather than to you about the TAPCIS connection. See that
  1226	message for my thoughts on the subject.
  1227	 
  1228	I just had another thought on this, looking and working with a thread graph
  1229	might be an amuzing application of VR technology.
  1230	 
  1231	BTW in order to REALLY make this work right we are going to need some way of
  1232	sensing the users head in relationship to the screen, so the software can do
  1233	the "looking around an object" bit. Ultrasonic transducers at the corners of
  1234	the screen and a little microphone on the glasses would probably work quite
  1235	well. I did a system like this awhile back, on a much larger scale, tracking
  1236	the position of a person in a room. Given the slow speed of sound, the
  1237	hardware is quite simple. Send out a pulse and start a counter, when the pulse
  1238	comes back in from the mic, stop the counter. Of course you have to worry
  1239	about ambient noise, but that is actually fairly easy to handle with digital
  1240	phase locked loop apprroaches.
  1241	 
  1242	John S.
  1243	       
