  1265	#: 21490 S13/Virtual Reality
  1266	    13-Nov-91  09:21:27
  1267	Sb: #21467-#Virtual Reality Forum
  1268	Fm: Chris Eisnaugle 76166,1257
  1269	To: John Eagan/VR 76130,2225 (X)
  1270	
  1271	John, I agree a lot of development is done on DOS but other machines do lend
  1272	themselves nicely to graphics developement and def cannot be ignored even in
  1273	the first go round (I Mean even if they arent developed for at the start they
  1274	def have to be kept in mind when designing and there strengths and weaknesses
  1275	addressed as well). As to the TI 320xx chip, about 2 yrs ago i was working on
  1276	an imaging system and the TI chips were ones we explored for using in a
  1277	display bored for our system. The chip is really nice in that it offers
  1278	(32020) about 12-15 mips graphics performance and includes a large set up
  1279	built in primatives for drawing, scaling, rotatiting, off screen drawing, and
  1280	just about any other graphic primative you might need. My suggestion into
  1281	integrating a chip like this into the helmet was not only to give a leg up on
  1282	primatives for rendering, and drawing but back to the main issue keeping the
  1283	VR work somewhat system independent. If the helmet was linked via the
  1284	Parrallel or Serial port and update packets (fromt he host) were sent to the
  1285	helmet (Which would need to have other chips to run the 320xx and receive data
  1286	etc) it could render seens pretty much instantly removing the drawing job from
  1287	the host thus freeing it do go onto the next task it had to perform etc. And
  1288	software that used a sort of update packet driven scheme could easily be
  1289	written machine independent. But like i said something like this is  prob in
  1290	the future or way off base, but thought id throw it into the fray <G>. But you
  1291	may be right in that initial software (primatives, Libs, and controllers)
  1292	should be written for prototyping etc. Has there ever been any thought to
  1293	creating your own glove using motion sensors etc? Also went looking for the
  1294	powerglove and couldnt find it, did they stop selling it? Also what kind of
  1295	cost does it incur to purcahse this thing <G>.
  1296	
  1297	Anyhow had thought about a helmet before so thought id ask <G>.
  1298	
  1299	Chris Eisnaugle
