  1374	#: 21512 S13/Virtual Reality
  1375	    13-Nov-91  13:51:41
  1376	Sb: #21454-great timing
  1377	Fm: Mike Schoenborn 70010,147
  1378	To: Bill Pulver 70405,1152 (X)
  1379	
  1380	Bill -
  1381	 
  1382	Ever since I was a child I have taken the expression "Don't!" as a call to
  1383	action, especially when it involved taking things apart. Thanks, I needed that.
  1384	 
  1385	The glasses can indeed be taken apart with nothing more than a pocket knife.
  1386	The 2 LCDs are mounted on a frame stuck in a sunglasses "shell", and can be
  1387	eaily, carefully, pried out without damage. (There is a contact point on
  1388	either side, 3 across the top, 2 on the bottom; you'll see what I mean when
  1389	yours are delivered).  The polarizers are part of the LCDs themselves, not
  1390	the sunglass plastic.
  1391	 
  1392	Without the sunglasses, the lenses pass a *lot* of light.  I don't know the
  1393	proper terminology to use here, but I want to say it seems like there is now
  1394	5% attenuation instead of 35.  Color images come through wonderfully without
  1395	having to max out the brightness control, and you can work much better with
  1396	room lights on.  The downside is that flicker is very noticible.  Right now I
  1397	can put up with it to see raytraces in full color 3D (640x480x256x3? :-), but
  1398	I think when the novelty wears off, the flicker will become quite annoying.
  1399	 
  1400	Maybe "flip up" shades and little epoxy will do the trick.
  1401	       
