  1803	Guess what!  Logitech will be marketing a combination 3-button-2D, 5-button-3D
  1804	mouse (with a little ultrasonic tripod) "2nd quarter '92" and are offering a
  1805	programmer's interface and prototype mouse right now "in limited quantities." 
  1806	I've got a press release from them that you can find in the LOGITECH forum,
  1807	library 6, Announcements, file 3D.TXT.  The description mentions a "head
  1808	tracker mount" which seems to be included, and a "dual mode" allowing two mice
  1809	(one head-mounted, one hand-held) to be used simultaneously (it then goes on
  1810	to say that _four_ mice can be used simultaneously with one tripod--share your
  1811	VR with a friend!).  Interesting features will include audio in-out and a
  1812	suspend button that freezes mouse output so that it can be repositioned
  1813	(equivalent to lifting a 2d mouse off of the pad to reposition it).  It will
  1814	have both Mac and PC (and whatever) interfaces and only requires a serial port
  1815	interface.
  1816	
  1817	No word on pricing, of course, but I will be calling Logitech later this
  1818	morning to find out what the development kit is going for.  Hopefully, I can
  1819	leave a message with their response this evening.  If it's not too expensive
  1820	this might be an alternative to a homebrew powerglove/head position interface.
  1821	If Logitech makes enough noise (and they don't seem to be slouches in the
  1822	marketing area) we might see a lot of third-party support for this (heck, even
  1823	Microsoft included a LogiMouse driver in Win3 from day one).
