  1877	#: 21572 S13/Virtual Reality
  1878	    14-Nov-91  10:42:38
  1879	Sb: Language
  1880	Fm: Alexander Schipal 76137,326
  1881	To: All
  1882	
  1883	
  1884	What about doing the software in C++ instead of C ?
  1885	
  1886	The C++ 2.0 language definition is stable now, Borland C++ looks OK and
  1887	Microsoft C/C++ 7.0 will - hopefully - turn up sometime next year.
  1888	Macs/Ataris/Amigas should have comparable compilers by now.
  1889	
  1890	There's nothing more object-oriented than constructing a virtual world !
  1891	
  1892	It would also do the C people (including myself) good to do some object
  1893	oriented programming, because that's where a programmer's money will come from
  1894	in the next ten years. Learning experience ! Once you know how to handle it,
  1895	C++ is just more efficient and productive than C.
  1896	
  1897	OTOH, C++ certainly has some acceptance problems, not everybody wants to cough
  1898	up the money for a new compiler, and C++ might just slow down the real work
  1899	here.
  1900	
  1901	Another idea: Some kind of object-oriented database module is necessary for
  1902	keeping track of all the virtual thingies, their possible behaviour (methods)
  1903	and interactions. That's a tricky one. Are there some DB gurus around ?
  1904	
  1905	One of the most fascinating and daunting characteristics of VR software is
  1906	it's potentially limitless hierarchy of objects, rules and relationships.
  1907	Maybe we should open PHILOSOPHY and FLAME threads, eh?
  1908	
